- l our exposure to sectors that impact our and our clients' businesses, particularly those operating in the commercial and residential construction sectors, and the infrastructure and energy sectors;
- l volatility in pension plan asset values and liabilities, which may require cash contributions to the pension plans;
- l changes in spending levels for residential and commercial construction;
- l the availability of short-term credit lines or working capital facilities, which can assist us in connection with market cycles;
- l any impact of not maintaining investment grade debt rating on our cost of capital and on the cost of the products and services we purchase;
- l availability of raw materials and related fluctuating prices of raw materials, as well as of goods and services in general, in particular increases in prices as a result of inflation;
- l our ability to maintain and expand our distribution network and maintain favorable relationships with third parties who supply us with equipment and essential suppliers;
- l competition in the markets in which we o/ffer our products and services;
- l the impact of environmental cleanup costs and other remedial actions, and other liabilities relating to existing and/or divested businesses;
- l our ability to secure and permit aggregates reserves in strategically located areas;
- l the timing and amount of federal, state and local funding for infrastructure;
- l changes in our e/ffective tax rate;
- l our ability to comply and implement technologies that aim to reduce CO2 emissions in jurisdictions with carbon regulations in place;
- l the legal and regulatory environment, including environmental, energy, tax, antitrust, human rights and labor welfare, acquisition-related rules and regulations;
- l the e/ffects of currency fluctuations on our results of operations and financial conditions;

